  <section>
    <h2>Conditionals</h2>
    <p>
      Control flow in Ruby uses <code>if</code>, <code>elsif</code>, and <code>else</code>. 
      Ruby also supports logical operators like <code>&&</code> (AND), <code>||</code> (OR), 
      and <code>not</code> (NOT).
    </p>
    
    <pre><code># Basic if-else
a = 1
b = 2
c = 3
d = 4
e = 5
f = 6

if d > a
  puts 'd > a'
end

if e < b
  puts 'e < b'
else
  puts 'e > b'
end

# elsif (else-if)
if f < c
  puts 'f < c'
elsif not (e >= b) && (d >= b)
  puts 'e <= b && d >= b'
else
  puts 'e <= c && d <= b'
  if (a <= f) || (d <= b)
    puts 'a <= f || d <= b'
  end
end

# Ternary operator
result = a > b ? 'a is bigger' : 'b is bigger'
puts result</code></pre>
