  <section>
    <h2>Loops</h2>
    <p>
      Ruby provides several ways to iterate: <code>while</code>, <code>for</code>, <code>until</code>, 
      and the versatile <code>loop</code> construct. Each has its use cases.
    </p>
    
    <pre><code># While loop (decrementing)
x = 5
while x >= 1
  puts x
  x -= 1
end

# For loop with array
arr = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
for i in arr do
  puts i
end

# For loop with range
y = 10
for z in 1..5 do
  y = y * 2
  puts y
end

# Loop do (do-while equivalent)
x = 1
loop do
  puts x
  x *= 2
  break if x >= 10
end

# Until loop
p = 1
until p == 5 do
  puts p * 5
  p += 1
end</code></pre>
