  <section>
    <h2>Methods</h2>
    <p>
      Methods in Ruby are defined with the <code>def</code> keyword and can accept parameters. 
      Ruby methods automatically return the last evaluated expression, but you can use 
      <code>return</code> explicitly for early returns or clarity.
    </p>
    
    <pre><code># Simple method
def hi
  puts "hello there"
end

# Method with parameter
def greet(name)
  puts "hello #{name}"
end

# Method with implicit return
def double_it(i)
  i * 2
end

# Method with explicit return
def half_it(i)
  r = i / 2.0
  return r
end

# Calling methods
greet("Alice")
puts double_it(10)
puts half_it(9)</code></pre>
  </section>

